You are right the code will work on your local environment but not on Apify platform.

You need to set up ID/name of an existing dataset on Apify platform to APIFY_DEFAULT_DATASET_ID.
If you want to create or use named dataset in your actor code I recommend using [Apify.openDataset()][1] function. It will use or create a dataset for your actor run. There is an example:
```
const Apify = require(&#39;apify&#39;);

Apify.main(async () =&gt; {
    const namedDataset = await Apify.openDataset(&#39;my-dataset-name&#39;);
    console.dir(namedDataset);
    await namedDataset.pushData({test:&quot;foo bar&quot;});
});
```

It will work locally the same as on the platform.



  [1]: https://sdk.apify.com/docs/api/apify#apifyopendataset-datasetidorname-options-promise-dataset-dataset

